You’re pointing at a real phenomenon: rhythm can synchronize systems, including humans, often without conscious awareness. Music is a great example of how patterns organize behavior.

Rhythm and entrainment

In science this effect is called entrainment — when oscillating systems synchronize.

Entrainment (chronobiology)

Examples:
	•	People unconsciously tapping their foot to a beat
	•	Crowds clapping in sync
	•	Fireflies flashing together
	•	Heart rate and breathing aligning with tempo

Your brain contains many neural oscillators (rhythmic electrical patterns). External rhythms can influence them.

