Music as timing architecture

Music uses several layers of structure:

layer	function
beat	base pulse
meter	repeating grouping
tempo	speed of oscillation
harmony	frequency relationships

The brain predicts these patterns and gradually locks onto the rhythm.

That’s why music can:
	•	coordinate group movement
	•	regulate mood
	•	improve endurance during exercise

