The math behind rhythm

Rhythms can be described with the same mathematics used for waves.

Common pieces of that math include:
	•	frequency
	•	phase
	•	amplitude

All oscillatory systems — sound waves, brain waves, rotating bodies — can be analyzed with similar tools.

That’s where constants like π appear again, because oscillations naturally involve circular or periodic relationships.

